section.section:
The provisions of paragraph (1) of this subsection are superseded as follows:
In Annapolis, the hours may be fixed by the Mayor, Counselor, and Aldermen of the City of Annapolis;
In the Park Heights Redevelopment Area that is specified in the Park Heights Master Plan adopted by Baltimore City in 2006, the hours of sale begin at 9 a.m. each day;
In Caroline County, the hours of operation are from 6 a.m. to 2 a.m. the following day, on Monday through Sunday;
In Carroll County, the privileges conferred by a Class A beer, wine and liquor license may be exercised from 11 a.m. to 6 p.m. on Sunday;
In Frederick County holders of a Class A beer, wine and liquor (off-sale) license may sell beer, wine and liquor for off-premises consumption on:
Monday through Saturday, from 6 a.m. to 2 a.m. the following day; and
Sunday, from 11 a.m. to 2 a.m. the following day, if they hold a special Sunday opening permit;
In Kent County, the provisions of § 11-515 of this article apply;
In St. Mary's County, holders of a Class A-1 license may sell on Sunday; and
In Talbot County, the hours are from 8 a.m. to 12 midnight.
